Tunisia Jails Ben Ali Advisors, Former Senate Leader, TAP Says

-- B y   J i h e n   L a g h m a r i
-- 
2011-03-13T10:25:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-13/tunisia-jails-ben-ali-advisors-former-senate-leader-tap-says.html
  Tunisia  has jailed two former aides
of ousted President Zine El Abdidine Ben Ali and the former
leader of the senate, Tunisian state television reported, citing
the investigating judge in the case.  The two former advisers, Abdelaziz Ben Dhia and Abdelwahab
Abdallah, and the former senate leader Abdallah Kallal have been
under house arrest since Jan. 23 and are accused of
“embezzlement, obtaining money illegally and harming the
country’s interests,” state television reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jihen Laghmari via Cairo newsroom at 
 jlaghmari@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mahmoud Kassem at 
 mkassem1@bloomberg.net  